This paper deals with automated reasoning in probabilistic logic, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of linguistic quantifiers and qualitative terms also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the quantified syllogism, which is a logical inference rule, indicating a possible connection to logic in computer science (cs.LO). The probabilistic nature of the reasoning involved suggests a connection to cryptography and security (cs.CR), and the use of qualitative reasoning techniques suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
